    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-03-23T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-03-23T16:00:00-05:00" n="56"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d56">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">874.00/3–1346: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Representative in Bulgaria</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Barnes</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="77" xml:id="d56fn77">The text of this telegram is
                        substantially the same as the original draft prepared by the Secretary
                        himself.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-03-23T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 23, 1946—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>93. Personal for Barnes from the Secretary. In your telegram no. 236 of March 13,
                    1946 you state that the Moscow Agreement as to Bulgaria was conceived by the
                    Soviet Government alone. That is not correct. You also say that the Agreement
                    helps only the Soviet Union. I feel that you should know that it is in conflict
                    with the views of your Government as to the advantages to be derived by carrying
                    out in good faith the terms of the Moscow Agreement.</p>
                <p>I think, as you will understand, that it is important that while representing
                    this Government at Sofia you should be careful to refrain from making such
                    statements.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
